        <body>
            <div type="question">
                <p>What is the best book you've ever read and why?</p>
                <note type="word-limit">(at least 80 words)</note>
                <label type="level">
                    <span>B1</span>
                </label>
            </div>
            <div type="answer">
                <p>I read a lot of books. And in my view, the best book, I've ever read, it's &quot;D. &quot;, writting by Robert Harris.</p>
                <p/>
                <p>The story is inspired by a real fact. This story talks about Alfred Dreyfus affair but from the point of view of Picard.</p>
                <p>Picard is colonel in the french army, he discovered that Dreyfus is not guilty. And the reader can follow the investigation and the release of Dreyfus.</p>
                <p>Picard is an interesting character and an original point of view. Because you had a different look on the affair and on Dreyfus.</p>
                <p/>
                <p>This story is wonderfull and very exciting. The style of harris is awesome and the book is very easy to read because it's a master piece.</p>
                <p/>
                <p>I suggest to everyone : &quot;D.&quot;</p>
                <p/>
                <p>Thank you for reading my review.</p>
            </div>
